goals.visualization: line chart of net_generation over year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there has been an increase or decrease in electricity generation over the years.

goals.question: What is the proportion of electricity generated from each source?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the contribution of each energy source to the total electricity generation.

goals.question: What is the distribution of net electricity generation for each source?
goals.visualization: box plot of net_generation over source
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread and central tendency of net electricity generation for each energy source.

goals.question: What is the trend in net electricity generation for each source?
goals.visualization: line chart of net_generation over year, with separate lines for each source
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there has been an increase or decrease in electricity generation for each energy source over the years.

goals.question: What is the correlation between net electricity generation and year?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a relationship between the year and net electricity generation.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend in net electricity generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum')
    data_pivot = data_pivot.div(data_pivot.sum(axis=1), axis=0)
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the proportion of electricity generated from each source?", wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.ylabel("Proportion")
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
